Glenashley Preparatory School in Durban North, managed to sell over 1 000 ‘Purple Heart Stickers’  recently, as part of their drive to create awareness around elder abuse. The learners raised over R5 000 for TAFTA. The school is also collecting toiletries for TAFTA’s toiletries wish-list. Pictured are Grade 5 learners Alex Botha and Alexia Swales receiving TAFTA’s Certificate of Appreciation for the school’s efforts.